# Quote template builder — Cursor handoff

## Stack
- Vite + React + TypeScript
- `dnd-kit` for canvas drag-and-drop
- `react-pdf` for preview rendering
- Zustand for global state (template, selected block, modal state)
- Tailwind CSS for styling

---

## Canvas layout grid

The quote document canvas uses a **strict 2-column grid** only. Blocks are either **50%** (half — one column) or **100%** (full — spans both columns). There is no 3-column or free-form layout.

Layout is stored per block as `content.layoutColumn`:
- `'full'` — 100% width row
- `'left'` + adjacent `'right'` — paired 50% / 50% row
- `'left'` alone — 50% width with empty right column (half_or_full blocks only)

### Allowed width by block

| Block | Attributes / merge vars | Width |
|-------|----------------------|-------|
| Company logo | Logo / image | **50% only** |
| Company address | Address lines (org address from business profile) | **50% only** |
| Quote summary | Quote #, date, expiry, customer id, payment terms | 50% or 100% |
| TCV summary | TC value, billing cycles, first billing amount | 50% or 100% |
| Billed to | Customer name, address, zip, city (billing address) | 50% or 100% |
| Contract details | Sub id, dates, length, frequency, billing cycles, contract TCV, renewal | 50% or 100% |
| Pricing table | Items, ramps, summary per period | **100% only** |
| Terms & conditions | Conditional legal segments | **100% only** |
| Entitlements | Feature, included, notes | 50% or 100% |
| Signature | Customer, vendor, date for each | 50% or 100% |
| AE details | Name, email, photo | 50% or 100% |

Implementation: `src/lib/block-layout-rules.ts` (`BLOCK_WIDTH_RULES`, `BLOCK_LAYOUT_ATTRIBUTES`). Enforced in `src/lib/block-layout.ts` via `normalizeBlockLayout`, `canAddBesideBlock`, and `setBlockCanvasWidth`.

Default blank template pairs **Company logo** (left) + **Company address** (right) in the first row. Pricing and terms are always full width.

Hover a block → **50% / 100%** control in block chrome toggles width when the block allows both.

---

## Data types

```ts
type BlockType =
  | 'header'
  | 'logo'
  | 'company_details'
  | 'billed_to'
  | 'quote_details'
  | 'pricing'
  | 'tcv_billing'
  | 'entitlements'
  | 'credits_tax'
  | 'terms'

type Block = {
  id: string
  type: BlockType
  order: number
  layout: {
    topPadding: number
    showBorder: boolean
  }
  content: Record<string, unknown> // varies per block type
}

type TermsBlock = Block & {
  type: 'terms'
  content: {
    text: string         // raw legal text
    spans: Span[]        // named regions within the text
    rules: Rule[]        // conditional rules referencing span ids
  }
}

type Span = {
  id: string
  name: string           // e.g. "prepaid-clause"
  start: number          // character offset in text
  end: number            // character offset in text
}

type Rule = {
  id: string
  spanId: string         // references Span.id
  condition: Condition
}

type Condition = {
  field: string          // e.g. "payment_terms", "customer.region"
  operator: 'is' | 'is_not' | 'gt' | 'lt' | 'contains'
  value: string
}

type Template = {
  id: string
  name: string
  status: 'draft' | 'published' | 'archived'
  blocks: Block[]
  routingRules: TemplateRoutingRule[]
  createdAt: string
  updatedAt: string
}

type TemplateRoutingRule = {
  id: string
  priority: number       // lower = evaluated first
  condition: Condition
  templateId: string
}

type TestScenario = {
  label: string
  values: Record<string, string>  // e.g. { payment_terms: 'Prepaid', customer_region: 'EU' }
}
```

---

## Global state (Zustand)

```ts
type Store = {
  // Template being edited
  template: Template | null
  setTemplate: (t: Template) => void

  // Canvas
  selectedBlockId: string | null
  setSelectedBlockId: (id: string | null) => void
  reorderBlocks: (from: number, to: number) => void

  // Modals
  tcRuleBuilderOpen: boolean
  openTCRuleBuilder: () => void
  closeTCRuleBuilder: () => void

  previewOpen: boolean
  openPreview: () => void
  closePreview: () => void
  activeScenario: TestScenario | null
  setActiveScenario: (s: TestScenario) => void
}
```

---

## Component tree

```
<App>
  <TemplatesLibrary>           // default route: /templates
    <TemplateCard />           // per template: name, status badge, last edited
    <NewTemplateButton />      // triggers new template flow

  <NewTemplateFlow>            // route: /templates/new
    step: 'upload' | 'processing' | 'picker'

    [step === 'upload']
      <UploadZone
        onFilesAdded={(files: File[]) => void}
      />
      <FileList
        files: File[]
        onRemove={(file: File) => void}
      />
      <GenerateButton
        disabled={files.length === 0}
        onClick={() => startGeneration(files)}
      />
      <StartBlankButton />

    [step === 'processing']
      <ProcessingSteps
        steps: ProcessingStep[]   // label + status: 'done' | 'active' | 'idle'
      />

    [step === 'picker']
      <VariantGrid>
        <VariantCard
          variant: GeneratedVariant    // name, sourceNote, tags, blockStack
          selected: boolean
          onClick: () => void
        />
      </VariantGrid>
      <RegenerateLink />
      <OpenInCanvasButton
        disabled={!selectedVariant}
        onClick={() => navigate(`/templates/${newId}/edit`)}
      />

  <CanvasEditor>               // route: /templates/:id/edit
    <TopBar>
      <Breadcrumb />
      <PreviewButton onClick={openPreview} />
      <SaveDraftButton />
      <PublishButton />

    <EditorBody>               // flex row: tray | canvas | sidebar
      <BlockTray>
        <TrayBlock
          type: BlockType
          active: boolean      // true if this type is already on canvas
          onDragStart: () => void
        />

      <Canvas>                 // dnd-kit drop target
        <SortableBlock
          block: Block
          selected: boolean
          onClick: () => setSelectedBlockId(block.id)
          // shows block label + content preview
          // T&C block shows rule count badge
          // drag handle on hover
        />
        <CanvasEmptyState />   // shown when no blocks added yet

      <PropertiesPanel>        // conditional on selectedBlockId
        [no selection]
          <TemplateLevelSettings />   // template name, page margins

        [block selected, type !== 'terms']
          <BlockHeader
            title: string      // e.g. "Pricing block"
            onClose: () => setSelectedBlockId(null)
          />
          <LayoutSection>
            // order, top padding, show border
          <ContentSection>
            // fields vary per BlockType (see per-block props below)

        [block selected, type === 'terms']
          <BlockHeader title="T&C block" />
          <LayoutSection />
          <OpenRuleBuilderButton onClick={openTCRuleBuilder} />
          // shows span count + rule count summary

  <TCRuleBuilder>              // full-screen modal, rendered inside CanvasEditor
    open: boolean
    onClose: closeTCRuleBuilder

    <TCTopBar>
      <BackButton onClick={closeTCRuleBuilder} />
      <SaveAndCloseButton />

    <TCBody>                   // flex row: editor | rules panel
      <TermsEditor>
        text: string
        spans: Span[]
        onTextChange: (text: string) => void
        onSpanCreate: (start: number, end: number) => void
        // renders colored underlines for each span
        // selection toolbar appears on highlight: "Mark as span"
        <SelectionHint />      // "Highlight text, then click Add rule"

      <RulesPanel>
        <RulesPanelHeader>
          <RuleCount />
          <AddRuleButton />    // adds a new empty rule card

        <RuleList>
          <RuleCard
            rule: Rule
            span: Span         // resolved from rule.spanId
            onConditionChange: (field, op, value) => void
            onSpanChange: (spanId: string) => void
            onDelete: () => void
          />

        <RuleSimulator>
          scenarios: TestScenario[]
          activeScenario: TestScenario
          onScenarioChange: (s: TestScenario) => void
          resolvedSpans: string[]   // span ids that are visible for active scenario

  <PreviewMode>                // full-screen mode, toggled via openPreview
    open: boolean
    onClose: closePreview

    <PreviewTopBar>
      <ExitButton onClick={closePreview} />
      <ScenarioPicker
        scenarios: TestScenario[]
        active: TestScenario
        onChange: setActiveScenario
      />
      <ExportPDFButton />

    <PreviewBody>              // flex row: pdf view | annotations panel
      <PDFView
        template: Template
        scenario: TestScenario
        // renders blocks in order
        // T&C text: only shows spans whose rules pass for active scenario
      />
      <AnnotationsPanel>
        <ActiveRuleList
          rules: Rule[]
          spans: Span[]
          resolvedSpans: string[]   // which span ids are on for this scenario
        />
        <ScenarioValues
          scenario: TestScenario
        />
```

